  "sections": {
    "Background": {
      "text": "Neurodegenerative disorder (dementia)\nMore rapid progression than Alzheimer's or\nParkinson's disease",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "Parkinson's disease",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Parkinson%27s_disease"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "Fluctuating cognition\nRecurrent visual\nhallucinations\nParkinsonian motor symptoms (cogwheel rigidity, shuffling gait, retropulsion)\nREM-sleep disturbance\nNeuroleptic sensitivity,  increased risk for\nneuroleptic malignant syndrome\nAcute worsening of cognition or delirium, with\nantipsychotics\n,\nbenzodiazepines\n,\nanticholinergics\n, surgical anesthetics",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "hallucinations",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Hallucinations"
        },
        {
          "text": "neuroleptic malignant syndrome",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Neuroleptic_malignant_syndrome"
        },
        {
          "text": "antipsychotics",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Antipsychotics"
        },
        {
          "text": "benzodiazepines",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Benzodiazepines"
        },
        {
